E%3Cem%3EEVAuto%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%2C%20an%20all-electric%20used%20car%20dealership%20in%20Bountiful%2C%20Utah%2C%20which%20he%20co-founded%20in%202019.%20The%20business%20now%20has%20anywhere%20from%2025%20to%2045%20cars%20on%20the%20lot%20at%20any%20given%20time%2C%20he%20said.%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20interview%20has%20been%20edited%20for%20length%20and%20clarity.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20first%20business%20was%20car%20detailing.%20I%20went%20door%20to%20door%20in%20wealthy%20neighborhoods%20near%20where%20I%20lived%20and%20asked%20if%20I%20could%20detail%20their%20car.%20Cars%20have%20always%20been%20a%20huge%20interest%20of%20mine.%20I%20put%20every%20possible%20dollar%20into%20my%20first%20car.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20was%20also%20always%20an%20early%20adopter%20of%20gadgets%2C%20software%2C%20and%20hardware.%20I%20spent%20the%20first%20half%20of%20my%20career%20in%20food%20franchising.%20Along%20the%20way%2C%20I%20was%20involved%20in%20starting%20and%20launching%20and%20being%20a%20part%20of%20some%20really%20cool%20tech%20startups.%20I%20also%20started%20teaching%20as%20an%20adjunct%20every%20once%20in%20a%20while%2C%20got%20an%20MBA%2C%20and%20then%20joined%20to%20start%20an%20entrepreneurship%20program.%20I%20decided%20to%20get%20a%20PhD%2C%20and%20then%20got%20the%20startup%20itch.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EMy%20cofounder%20and%20I%20were%20talking%2C%20and%20he%20said%C2%A0'it's%20such%20a%20pain%20to%20buy%20or%20sell%20a%20used%20Tesla'%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EYou%20have%20to%20go%20to%20a%20bunch%20of%20different%20places%2C%20you%20have%20to%20deal%20with%20a%20bunch%20of%20different%20salespeople%2C%20probably%20have%20a%20bunch%20of%20different%20bad%20experiences.%20It%20takes%20a%20lot%20of%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%20in%202019%2C%20we%20acquired%20evcars.com%20and%20evtrucks.com%20with%20the%20intention%20to%20build%20a%20marketplace%20for%20other%20people%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fused-e