tps%3A%2F%2Fwww-bbc-co-uk.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fbusiness-67254006.amp%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fbusiness-67254006.amp%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Meet%20the%20typical%20retail%20worker%3A%20an%20elder%20millennial%20woman%20earning%20%2418%20hourly%20picking%20online%20Walmart%20orders%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22walmart%20worker%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F5b0edca942e1cc62b218d37c%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221333%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EWalmart%20employs%20about%2010%25%20of%20the%20nation's%20retail%20workers.%20%3Cp%3EJulio%20Cortez%2FAP%20Photos%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20US%20has%20roughly%2015.5%20million%20retail%20workers%2C%20while%201.5%20million%20Americans%20work%20for%20Walmart.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EWalmart's%20workforce%20is%20at%20least%20three%20times%20larger%20than%20that%20of%20any%20other%20brick-and-mortar%20retailer.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20company's%20typical%20worker%20is%20a%2039-year-old%20woman%20in%20Dallas%20earning%20%2418%20per%20hour.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20the%20largest%20private%20employer%20in%20the%20world%2C%20in%20the%20US%2C%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flargest-employers-each-us-state-2017-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ein%20many%20states%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Walmart%20is%20in%20many%20ways%20representative%20of%20the%20wider%20retail%20industry.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20company%20employs%20over%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcorporate.walmart.com%2Fcontent%2Fdam%2Fcorporate%2Fdocuments%2Fpurpose%2Fculture-diversity-equity-and-inclusion-report%2F2023-culture-diversity-equity-and-inclusion-annual-report.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E1.5%20million%3C%2Fa%3E%20US%20workers%2C%20or%20roughly%20one-tenth%20of%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bls.gov%2Fnews.release%2Fempsit.t17.htm%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E15.5%20million%3C%2Fa%3E%20people%20employed%20in%20the%20sector.%20A%20workforce%20that%20size%20means%20a%20worker%20is%20at%20least%20three%20times%20as%20likely%20to%20work%20for%20Walmart%20than%20for%20any%20single%20other%20brick-and-mortar%20retailer.%20%3Cspan%3EIn%20fact%2C%20Walmart%20employs%20more%20workers%20in%20the%20US%20than%20the%20next%20three%20largest%20physical%20retailers%20combined%3A%20Target%2C%20Kroger%2C%20and%20Home%20Depot.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThose%20employees%20live%20and%20work%20in%20all%2050%20states%2C%20where%20the%20company%20operates%20over%205%2C200%20locations%2C%20from%20big%20cities%20to%20small%20towns%20and%20beyond.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20ever%20there%20was%20a%20%26quot%3Btypical%26quot%3B%20retail%20worker%2C%20it%20is%20safe%20to%20say%20they%20work%20for%20Walmart.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20also%20safe%20to%20say%20she's%20a%20woman%20(53%25%20of%20the%20company's%20hourly%20workers%20are)%2C%20she's%20white%20(half%20of%20employees%20identify%20as%20Caucasian%2C%20half%20identify%20as%20non-Caucasian%20ethnicities)%2C%20and%20a%20so-called%20%26quot%3Belder%20millennial%26quot%3B%20(the%20average%20age%20is%20about%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E39)%2C%20based%20on%20company%20reports.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20would%20also%20work%20at%20a%20Supercenter%20near%20Dallas%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcorporate.walmart.com%2Fabout%2Flocation-facts%2Funited-states%2Ftexas%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ETexas%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20where%20the%20company%20told%20Insider%20it%20has%20the%20highest%20density%20of%20stores.%20The%20state%20is%20home%20to%20about%20500%20Walmart%20stores%20and%2081%20Sam's%20Club%20warehouses%2C%20and%20over%20175%2C000%20workers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHer%20job%20assignment%20is%20most%20likely%20to%20be%20either%20a%20stocker%2C%20who%20refills%20shelves%20with%20merchandise%2C%20or%20a%20digital%20picker%2C%20who%20collects%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwalmart-gets-into-the-replenishment-game-16-years-after-amazon-2023-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eorders%20for%20online%20shoppers%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20company%20told%20Insider.%20Either%20way%2C%20she%20can%20be%20found%20in%20the%20aisles%20of%20the%20store%20either%20putting%20items%20on%20the%20shelves%20or%20taking%20them%20off.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAlthough%20she%20might%20be%20demographically%20%26quot%3Btypical%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20job%20she%20does%20is%20anything%20but%2C%20a%20worker%20in%20Illinois%20told%20Insider.%20The%20worker%20requested%20that%20their%20name%20not%20be%20used%2C%20as%20they%20are%20not%20authorized%20to%20speak%20to%20the%20media.%20Insider%20has%20verified%20their%20identity%20and%20employment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20amount%20of%20sales%20that%20a%20typical%20Supercenter%20does%20is%20crazy.%20It's%20almost%20like%20Christmas%20at%20any%20other%20retail%20place%20every%20weekend%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20person%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMore%20than%20two-thirds%20of%20hourly%20Walmart%20workers%20are%20full-time%2C%20meaning%20they%20work%20an%20average%20of%20at%20least%2034%20hours%20per%20week%20%E2%80%94%20an%20unusually%20high%20percentage%20among%20retailers%2C%20where%20the%20industry%20average%20is%20less%20than%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ffred.stlouisfed.org%2Fseries%2FAWHAERT%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E30%20hours%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Walmart%20employees%20who%20work%20at%20least%2030%20hours%20per%20week%20are%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwalmart-expanding-telehealth-benefit-to-million-employees-2023-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eeligible%20to%20receive%20health%20benefits%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERetail%20in%20general%20sees%20some%20of%20the%20highest%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ffred.stlouisfed.org%2Fgraph%2F%3Fg%3D1aIow%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elabor%20turnover%3C%2Fa%3E%20rates%20of%20any%20sector%2C%20but%20Walmart's%20typical%20employee%20has%20been%20with%20the%20company%20for%20five%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECEO%20Doug%20McMillon%20famously%20started%20with%20the%20company%20as%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwalmart-ceo-doug-mcmillon-bio-career-life-salary-first-job-2021-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehourly%20employee%20on%20the%20loading%20docks%3C%2Fa%3E%20before%20rising%20to%20the%20C-suite%2C%20and%20three-quarters%20of%20Walmart's%20salaried%20managers%20started%20out%20in%20hourly%20roles.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe're%20constantly%20working%20to%20bring%20our%20values%20to%20life%20through%20our%20culture%20and%20strengthen%20the%20ladder%20of%20opportunity%2C%26quot%3B%20McMillon%20has%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAbout%205%25%20of%20all%20US%20workers%20hold%20multiple%20jobs%2C%20and%20the%20Illinois%20employee%20said%20several%20of%20their%20coworkers%20worked%20another%20full-%20or%20part-time%20job%20or%20did%20gig%20work%20when%20they%20weren't%20at%20Walmart.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20you%20work%20a%20regular%20nine-to-five%2C%20you%20could%20still%20work%20a%20closing%20shift%20or%20the%20weekends%20here%20because%20we're%20open%20until%2011%20p.m.%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20worker%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWalmart%20told%20Insider%20it%20does%20not%20keep%20track%20of%20how%20many%20jobs%20associates%20have%20at%20a%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20600%2C000%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Epeople%20work%20for%20Walmart%20outside%20the%20US%2C%20and%20while%20the%20worldwide%20median%20employee%20earned%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fd18rn0p25nwr6d.cloudfront.net%2FCIK-0000104169%2F962f88b9-c501-4834-84c8-a95022bdd444.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%2427%2C136%3C%2Fa%3E%20last%20year%2C%20the%20typical%20worker%20in%20Texas%20likely%20makes%20a%20good%20bit%20more.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20typical%20employee%20likely%20earns%