9s%20Witnesses%20near%20Kochi.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fsecurity%2Fone-dead-more-than-36-injured-in-serial-blasts-at-christian-prayer-meet-in-kerala%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22They%20got%20out%20of%20prison.%20Then%20the%20city%20gave%20them%20%247%2C200%20%E2%80%94%20no%20strings%20attached.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20woman%20and%20her%20family%20in%20front%20of%20a%20globe%20collage%20of%20money%2C%20childcare%20and%20work.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6538417e356802a56be2eb61%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAll%20across%20America%2C%20the%20evidence%20is%20overwhelming%3A%20Universal%20basic%20income%20is%20working.%3Cp%3EChelsea%20Jia%20Feng%2FInsider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20spring%20of%202022%2C%20Tydricka%20Lewis%20finally%20bought%20a%20car%20that%20started%20every%20time%20she%20asked%20it%20to%20and%20no%20longer%20left%20her%20stranded.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHer%202020%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnissan-reveals-futuristic-electric-minivan-design-hyper-tourer2023-10%5C%22%3ENissan%3C%2Fa%3E%20Rogue%20was%20essential%20to%20her%20new%20job%20as%20a%20peer-support%20specialist%20%E2%80%94%20helping%20people%20in%20mental-health%20crises%20required%20her%20to%20be%20able%20to%20get%20places%20reliably%20and%20fast.%20And%20it%20was%20essential%20to%20her%20new%20life%20outside%20prison%2C%20where%20she'd%20spent%20six%20years%20and%20four%20months%20for%20chasing%20fraudulent%20checks.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20a%20car%20that%20Lewis%2C%20a%2032-year-old%20single%20mother%20of%20three%2C%20would%20not%20otherwise%20have%20been%20able%20to%20afford.%20But%20when%20she%20was%20selected%20for%20Durham%2C%20North%20Carolina's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhat-is-basic-income-2016-8%5C%22%3Eguaranteed-income%3C%2Fa%3E%20pilot%20program%2C%20she%20knew%20exactly%20where%20her%20%24600%20monthly%20stipend%20would%20be%20best%20spent.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20late%202020%2C%20then-Twitter%20CEO%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjack-dorsey-twitter-creator-billionaire%5C%22%3EJack%20Dorsey%3C%2Fa%3E%20pledged%20%2415%20million%20to%20the%20national%20advocacy%20group%20Mayors%20for%20a%20Guaranteed%20Income%20to%20help%20select%20cities%20and%20towns%20across%20America%20kick-start%20basic-income%20programs.%20Durham%20was%20one%20of%2025%20recipients%20and%20received%20%24500%2C000%20from%20Dorsey%20and%20another%20%24500%2C000%20from%20local%20philanthropy%20and%20the%20city's%20coffers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDurham's%20mayor%20pro%20tempore%2C%20Mark-Anthony%20Middleton%2C%20who%20helped%20oversee%20the%20program%2C%20had%20been%20advocating%20for%20his%20city%20to%20introduce%20a%20basic%20income%20for%20years.%20%26quot%3BWe%20wanted%20to%20see%20what%20a%20stream%20of%20income%2C%20without%20any%20determination%20of%20virtue%20or%20vice%20attached%20to%20it%2C%20would%20do%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20Durham's%20population%20has%20ballooned%2C%20many%20of%20its%20lower-income%20and%20Black%20residents%20have%20been%20pushed%20to%20the%20fringes.%20Once%20one%20of%20the%20South's%20centers%20of%20Black%20commerce%2C%20with%20its%20own%20Black%20Wall%20Street%2C%20the%20vibrant%20Hayti%20community%2C%20home%20to%20the%20renowned%20historically%20Black%20North%20Carolina%20Central%20University%2C%20Durham%20has%20become%20much%20whiter%20%E2%80%94%20by%2051%25%20over%20the%20past%2020%20years%2C%20according%20to%20US%20Census%20data.%20And%20as%20wealthier%20residents%20moved%20in%2C%20Durham's%20median%20home%20price%20rose%20by%20more%20than%2050%25%20between%202010%20and%202019.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%20the%20city%20decided%20that%20all%20of%20the%20%241%20million%20in%20basic-income%20funds%20would%20go%20to%20a%20single%2C%20vulnerable%20group%3A%20formerly%20incarcerated%20residents.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMany%20taxpayers%20were%20not%20happy%20about%20this.%20As%20the%20program%20neared%20its%20launch%20in%20March%202022%2C%20Middleton's%20inbox%20and%20mailbox%20were%20flooded%20with%20messages%20filled%20with%20epithets.%20They%20came%20from%20white%20residents%20in%20the%20more%20conservative%20counties%20near%20Durham%20to%20recent%20transplants%20from%20liberal%20strongholds%20like%20New%20York%20City%20and%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcalifornia-forever-silicon-valley-billionaire-city-plans-are-terrible-2023-9%5C%22%3EBay%20Area%3C%2Fa%3E.%20They%20demanded%20to%20know%20why%20the%20city%20was%20underwriting%20criminals%2C%20disincentivizing%20work%20with%20free%20handouts%2C%20and%20spending%20public%20dollars%20to%20help%20people%20who%2C%20in%20some%20opinions%2C%20might%20not%20deserve%20help.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMiddleton's%20answer%20to%20all%20criticism%20was%20steadfast%2C%20simple%2C%20and%20by%20his%20own%20admission%2C%20%26quot%3Bvery%20selfish.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe're%20going%20to%20have%20to%20pay%20for%20these%20people%20one%20way%20or%20another%2C%20either%20in%20incarceration%2C%20benefits%2C%20homeless%20shelters%2C%20whatever%20it%20is%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20told%20me.%20%26quot%3BIt%20seems%20to%20me%20that%20spending%20more%20money%20up%20front%20makes%20more%20sense%20than%20housing%20folks%2C%20monitoring%20and%20feeding%20them%2C%20and%20taking%20care%20of%20their%20healthcare%20in%20prison.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20encourages%20skeptical%20taxpayers%20to%20look%20at%20universal%20basic%20income%20from%20the%20same%20%26quot%3Bselfish%20point%20of%20view.%26quot%3B%20%26quot%3BBy%20virtue%20of%20your%20humanity%2C%20your%20citizenship%2C%20and%20your%20residency%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added%2C%20%26quot%3Bthere's%20a%20certain%20line%20we%20will%20not%20allow%20you%20to%20fall%20under%20because%20it's%20good%20policy%20for%20us.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThough%20the%20data%20is%20still%20nascent%2C%20basic%20income%20has%20proven%20to%20be%20good%20policy%20everywhere%20it's%20been%20tested%20in%20America.%20The%20Durham%20program%20would%20be%20one%20of%20its%20greatest%20tests%20yet.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20idea%20that%20the%20government%20should%20guarantee%20all%20citizens%20a%20set%20amount%20of%20money%20has%20been%20discussed%20at%20the%20margins%20of%20American%20policy%20throughout%20the%20nation's%20history.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20his%201797%20pamphlet%20%26quot%3BAgrarian%20Justice%2C%26quot%3B%20Thomas%20Paine%20argued%20that%20all%20citizens%20had%20the%20right%20to%20a%20guaranteed%20lump%20sum%20when%20they%20became%20adults.%20During%20the%20Great%20Depression%2C%20Louisiana's%20governor%2C%20Huey%20Long%2C%20proposed%20a%20guaranteed%20annual%20household%20income%20of%20%242%2C000%20to%20%243%2C000%20(some%20%2440%2C000%20to%20%2460%2C000%20in%202023).%20In%201972%2C%20when%20Senator%20George%20McGovern%20was%20running%20for%20president%2C%20he%20proposed%20writing%20a%20%241%2C000%20check%20annually%20to%20every%20American.%20Though%20the%20concept%20faltered%20in%20the%20Reaganomics%20era%20of%20the%201980s%20and%20the%20Clintonomics%20of%20the%201990s%2C%20talk%20of%20a%20universal%20basic%20income%20reemerged%20during%20the%202020%20presidential-election%20campaign%2C%20when%20it%20became%20a%20major%20platform%20point%20of%20the%20candidate%20Andrew%20Yang.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cblockquote%3E%3Cq%3E%26quot%3BWhat's%20helpful%20about%20cash%20is%20that%20it's%20cash%2C%20and%20you%20can%20use%20it%20for%20whatever%20you%20need.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fq%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%3Cp%3EA%20large%20part%20of%20the%20renewed%20interest%20is%20that%20%26quot%3Bwe%20have%20a%20higher%20degree%20of%20inequality%20now%20than%20we%20did%20before%20the%20Great%20Depression%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Anna%20Jefferson%2C%20a%20principal%20investigator%20at%20Abt%20Associates%20who%20studies%20data%20from%20basic-income%20programs%20across%20the%20country.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20past%20few%20years%2C%20aided%20no%20doubt%20by%20the%20economic%20consequences%20wrought%20by%20the%20pandemic%2C%20centuries%20of%20theory%20have%20at%20last%20been%20put%20to%20the%20test.%20A%20few%20dozen%20cities%20across%20the%20country%20have%20begun%20basic-income%20programs%2C%20and%20the%20early%20results%20have%20been%20overwhelmingly%20positive.%20In%20Denver%2C%20more%20than%20800%20of%20the%20city's%20most%20vulnerable%20residents%20received%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fubi-cash-payments-reduced-homelessness-increased-employment-denver-2023-10%5C%22%3Emonthly%20stipends%20of%20up%20to%20%241%2C000%3C%2Fa%3E.%20So%20far%20the%20program%20has%20reduced%20homelessness%2C%20increased%20employment%2C%20and%20bolstered%20the%20mental-health%20outcomes%20of%20participants.%20A%20similar%20program%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstockton-california-basic-income-experiment-unemployment-decline-2021-3%5C%22%3EStockton%2C%20California%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20had%20similar%20effects%20%E2%80%94%20the%20unemployment%20rate%20among%20the%20125%20participants%20was%20nearly%20halved.%20Researchers%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Pennsylvania%20studying%20the%20program%20concluded%20it%20could%20have%20%26quot%3Bprofound%20positive%20impacts%20on%20local%20public%20health.%26quot%3B%3Cq%3E%3C%2Fq%3E%3Cq%3E%3C%2Fq%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPilot%20programs%20have%20sprung%20up%20across%20the%20country%2C%20from%20liberal%20strongholds%20such%20as%20Los%20Angeles%20and%20Baltimore%20to%20more%20centrist%20and%20conservative%20cities%20like%20Columbia%2C%20South%20Carolina%3B%20Birmingham%2C%20Alabama%3B%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fflorida-basic-income-pilot-formerly-incarcerated-money-2021-11%5C%22%3EGainesville%2C%20Florida%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Just%20Income%2C%20the%20Florida%20program%2C%20also%20focused%20its%20stipends%20on%20formerly%20incarcerated%20individuals%2C%20with%20a%20rationale%20similar%20to%20Middleton's.%20%26quot%3BIt%20costs%20Floridians%20about%20%2428%2C000%20a%20year%20to%20hold%20someone%20in%20prison%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20director%20of%20the%20Gainesville%20program%20said%20in%20a%20press%20release%20earlier%20this%20year.%20%26quot%3BAlternatively%2C%20we're%20investing%20just%20%247%2C600%20directly%20to%20one%20of%20our%20valued%20neighbors%2C%20giving%20them%20a%20vital%20income%20floor.%26quot%3B%20In%20city%20after%20city%20and%20cohort%20after%20cohort%20%E2%80%94%20old%2C%20young%2C%20single%20parents%2C%20ex-convicts%20%E2%80%94%20universal%20basic%20income%20has%20improved%20health%20outcomes%2C%20raised%20employment%2C%20and%20bolstered%20childcare%20opportunities%20(and%20recipients%20have%20had%20consistently%20better%20outcomes%20than%20control%20groups).%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225546%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22stockton%20california%20universal%20basic%20income%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F653c19ed356802a56be68a8c%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%224160%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAmong%20those%20who%20received%20a%20basic%20income%20in%20Stockton%2C%20California%2C%20the%20unemployment%20rate%20dropped%20by%20nearly%2050%25.%3Cp%3ENick%20Otto%2FAFP%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20Jefferson%2C%20guaranteed%20income%20%E2%80%94%20which%20she%20calls%20%26quot%3Bunrestricted%20cash%20transfers%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20impacts%20recipients'%20lives%20almost%20immediately.%20Early%20results%20from%20her%20firm's%20analysis%2C%20she%20said%2C%20%26quot%3Breally%20show%20that%20cash%20can%20improve%20people's%20financial%20stress%20and%20mental%20health%20remarkably%20and%20quickly.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20more%20data%20at%20hand%20than%20theoretical%20projection%2C%20the%20evidence%20is%20overwhelming%3A%20Universal%20basic%20income%20is%20working%20nearly%20universally.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20qualify%20for%20Durham's%20guaranteed-income%20program%2C%20which%20the%20city%20called%20Excel%2C%20applicants%20had%20to%20be%20Durham%20residents%2018%20years%20or%20older%2C%20incarcerated%20no%20later%20than%202016%2C%20and%20fall%20below%2060%25%20of%20the%20city's%20annual%20median%20incomee.%20From%20a%20pool%20of%20247%20eligible%20applicants%2C%20109%20were%20randomly%20selected%20to%20be%20recipients%2C%20and%20the%20rest%20were%20part%20of%20the%20control%20group.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20element%20that%20was%20essential%20to%20Middleton%20was%20that%20the%20money%20Excel%20handed%20out%20come%20with%20no%20strings%20attached.%20He%20wanted%20to%20see%20how%20the%20beneficiaries%20chose%20to%20use%20their%20money.%20None%20were%20required%20to%20check%20in%20with%20StepUp%20%E2%80%94%20the%20Durham-based%20nonprofit%20that%20administered%20the%20program%20%E2%80%94%20or%20the%20city%20to%20explain%20how%20and%20where%20they%20were%20using%20their%20income.%20There%20was%20no%20work%20requirement%20and%20no%20surveys%20to%20fill%20out.%20Recipients%20all%20received%20a%20debit%20card%20preloaded%20with%20%24600%20a%20month%20for%20a%20year%20%E2%80%94%20%247%2C200%20to%20spend%20as%20they%20pleased.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BFolks%20paid%20their%20rent%2C%20they%20bought%20clothes%20for%20their%20children%2C%20they%20bought%20medicine%2C%20some%20people%20took%20a%20weekend%20trip%2C%26quot%3B%20Middleton%20said.%20%26quot%3BMostly%2C%20people%20did%20normal%20stuff%3B%20they%20paid%20bills%20and%20bought%20food.%20Surprise%2C%20surprise.%26quot%3B%20Others%20paid%20off%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcollege-tuition-costs-too-much-make-degrees-matter-less-jobs-2023-9%23%3A~%3Atext%3DToday%2520some%252044%2520million%2520Americans%2Cworth%2520the%2520price%2520of%2520admission.%5C%22%3Elong-standing%20student%20loans%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJefferson%20has%20found%20this%20is%20typical%20of%20how%20basic-income%20recipients%20across%20the%20country%20spend%20their%20stipends.%20While%20it's%20difficult%20to%20pinpoint%20exactly%20where%20each%20dollar%20goes%2C%20the%20vast%20majority%20of%20recipients%20spend%20them%20on%20the%20basics%3A%20healthier%20food%2C%20school%20supplies%2C%20and%20extracurriculars%20or%20developmental%20support%20for%20their%20children.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhat's%20helpful%20about%20cash%20is%20that%20it's%20cash%2C%20and%20you%20can%20use%20it%20for%20whatever%20you%20need%2C%26quot%3B%20Jefferson%20said.%3Cq%3E%3C%2Fq%3E%3Cq%3E%3C%2Fq%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20she%20was%20released%20from%20prison%20in%202019%2C%20Tydricka%20Lewis%20cobbled%20together%20a%20living%20by%20holding%20two%2C%20sometimes%20three%2C%20jobs%20at%20once%2C%20including%20at%20a%20KFC%20and%20a%20Habitat%20for%20Humanity%20resource%20center.%20A%20few%20months%20after%20her%20release%2C%20she%20was%20certified%20as%20a%20peer-support%20specialist%20and%20began%20working%20with%20a%20nonprofit%20that%20provides%20community%20mental-health%20and%20substance-abuse%20treatment.%20She%20could%20have%20used%20her%20Excel%20money%20to%20buy%20food%20or%20clothes%20for%20her%20three%20children%2C%20who%20were%2018%2C%2011%2C%20and%203.%20But%20she%20saw%20a%20car%20as%20the%20lynchpin%20through%20which%20she%20could%20provide%20for%20her%20family%2C%20a%20foundation%20to%20hopefully%20pull%20them%20out%20of%20the%20poverty%20that%20she%20has%20been%20mired%20in%20for%20so%20much%20of%20her%20life.%20The%20Rogue%20also%20afforded%20Lewis%20peace%20of%20mind%2C%20knowing%20that%20she%20and%20her%20kids%20would%20no%20longer%20have%20to%20worry%20about%20the%20car's%20heater%20fritzing%20out%20in%20the%20middle%20of%20Durham's%20icy%20winters.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EBy%20all%20early%20accounts%2C%20Excel%20has%20been%20a%20resounding%20success.%20The%20employment%20rates%20and%20housing%20rates%20among%20the%20recipients%20have%20steadily%20climbed.%20And%20during%20the%20program's%20yearlong%20run%2C%20there%20was%20a%20zero-percent%20rate%20of%20recidivism.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cblockquote%3E%3Cq%3E%26quot%3BEconomically%20stable%20people%20make%20better%20neighbors.%20When%20they%20aren't%20worried%20about%20how%20they're%20going%20to%20pay%20their%20bills%2C%20they%20tend%20not%20to%20come%20through%20your%20window%20at%20night.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fq%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%3Cp%3EResearchers%20at%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Funiversity-of-pennsylvania-major-donors-pulling-funding-israel-hamas-war-2023-10%5C%22%3EUniversity%20of%20Pennsylvania%3C%2Fa%3E%20studying%20the%20program%20plan%20to%20have%20data%20comparing%20recipients'%20outcomes%20to%20the%20control%20group's%20outcomes%20in%202024.%20But%20based%20on%20early%20results%2C%20Durham%20County%20is%20now%20set%20to%20roll%20out%20a%20%24750-a-month%20guaranteed-income%20pilot%20to%20125%20local%20families%20who%20have%20children%20at%20home%20and%20fall%20beneath%2030%25%20of%20the%20county's%20annual%20median%20income.%20Meanwhile%2C%20Middleton%20has%20secured%20another%20%241%20million%20in%20the%20city's%20budget%20to%20continue%20the%20initiative%20with%20public%20dollars%2C%20which%20he%20hopes%20will%20kick%20off%20in%20mid-2024.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPromising%20as%20these%20pilot%20programs%20are%2C%20the%20chances%20of%20a%20truly%20%3Cem%3Euniversal%3C%2Fem%3E%20basic%20income%20in%20America%20remain%20remote.%20For%20one%2C%20empirical%20evidence%20does%20not%20equal%20political%20will.%20UBI%20researchers%20often%20point%20to%20Congress's%20decision%20not%20to%20renew%20the%20Covid-era%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchild-poverty-rate-america-congress-cut-biden-expanded-tax-credit-2023-9%23%3A~%3Atext%3DThe%2520expanded%2520CTC%2520meant%2520up%2Cbills%252C%2520as%2520Insider%2520has%2520reported.%5C%22%3EChild%20Tax%20Credit%20%3C%2Fa%3E%E2%80%94%20even%20though%20it%20slashed%20America's%20monthly%20child%20poverty%20rate%20by%2030%25%20%E2%80%94%20as%20a%20measure%20of%20how%20difficult%20passing%20a%20nationwide%20UBI%20would%20be.%20The%20main%20political%20roadblock%20is%20its%C2%A0cost.%C2%A0A%202022%20%3Cem%3EWashington%20Post%20%3C%2Fem%3Estory%20about%20UBI%20noted%20that%20%26quot%3Bproviding%20%241%2C000%20a%20month%20to%20every%20American%20regardless%20of%20income%26quot%3B%20would%20cost%20more%20than%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.washingtonpost.com%2Fmagazine%2F2022%2F10%2F24%2Funiversal-basic-income%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%243%20trillion%20a%20year%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%26quot%3Bnearly%20half%20the%20federal%20government's%20entire%20budget.%26quot%3B%20But%20as%20that%20same%20article%20noted%2C%20a%20mass%20of%20evidence%20suggests%20that%20%26quot%3Bpulling%20people%20out%20of%20poverty%20generates%20a%20huge%20increase%20in%20tax%20revenue%20as%20well%20as%20savings%20on%20public%20assistance%20programs.%26quot%3B%20And%20as%20Jefferson%20noted%2C%20if%20new%20pilot%20programs%20produce%20the%20same%20results%20as%20what's%20already%20been%20tested%2C%20they%20may%20help%20sway%20the%20court%20of%20public%20opinion%20yet.%20If%20still%20more%20data%20shows%2C%20she%20said%2C%20shows%20that%20guaranteed%20income%20%26quot%3Bis%20reducing%20the%20need%20for%20food%20assistance%20or%20housing%20subsidies%20or%20criminal%20justice%20systems%20or%20burdens%20on%20healthcare%20systems%2C%20it%20may%20be%20something%20that%20pays%20for%20itself.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20for%20Tydricka%20Lewis%2C%20basic%20income%20afforded%20her%20the%20latitude%20to%20start%20her%20own%20nonprofit.%20The%20New%20Generation%20Movement%20offers%20peer%20support%20to%20the%20kinds%20of%20young%2