0Israel%20to%20release%20all%20Palestinian%20prisoners%20from%20their%20jails%20in%20exchange%20for%20the%20hostages%20held%20by%20them%20in%20Gaza.%20Hostages%20have%20very%20high%20political%20currency%20and%20had%20been%20a%20major%20reason%20for%20negotiations%20in%20the%20past.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ESince%20its%20October%207%20attack%2C%20the%20Palestinian%20Hamas%20group%20had%20kidnapped%20over%20200%20civilians%20from%20Israeli%20border%20towns%20and%20dragged%20them%20across%20the%20Gazan%20border.%20These%20include%20several%20foreigners%20and%20dual%20citizenship%20holders.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHamas%20leader%20Yahya%20Sinwar%20recently%20said%20they%20are%20ready%20for%20an%20%26quot%3Bimmediate%26quot%3B%20prisoner%20swap%20with%20Israel.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20are%20ready%20to%20conduct%20an%20immediate%20prisoner%20exchange%20deal%20that%20includes%20the%20release%20of%20all%20Palestinian%20prisoners%20from%20Israeli%20jails%20in%20exchange%20for%20all%20prisoners%20held%20by%20the%20Palestinian%20resistance%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%20in%20a%20statement.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%202011%2C%20Israel%20swapped%201%2C027%20Palestinian%20prisoners%20to%20get%20a%20soldier%20released.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThis%20time%2C%20with%20so%20many%20hostages%20held%20by%20Hamas%20in%20a%20war%20zone%2C%20Israel%20faces%20one%20of%20the%20most%20complex%20hostage%20situations%20ever.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ENegotiations%20seem%20to%20have%20worked%20in%20favour%20of%20Israel%20so%20far%20with%20the%20intervention%20of%20US%20and%20Qatar%2C%20and%20four%20hostages%20have%20been%20released.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EHostages%20for%20ceasefire%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIsrael%20believes%20in%20not%20leaving%20anyone%20behind%2C%20dead%20or%20alive.%20Hamas%20has%20offered%20the%20release%20of%20all%20hostages%20in%20exchange%20of%20a%20ceasefire%2C%20but%20Prime%20Minister%20Benjamin%20Netanyahu%20-%20who%20has%20already%20declared%20a%20war%20against%20Hamas%2