wer%20correct%2C%20it%20received%20a%20treat%2C%20the%20release%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThrough%20trial%20and%20error%2C%20the%20pigeons%20improved%20their%20performance%20from%2055%25%20to%2095%25%20correct%20answers%20in%20one%20easier%20task%2C%20according%20to%20the%20release.%20Researchers%20performed%20the%20same%20tests%20using%20AI%20and%20found%20the%20AI%20also%20learned%20to%20decrease%20its%20amount%20of%20mistakes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20study%2C%20published%20in%20the%20journal%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cell.com%2Fiscience%2Ffulltext%2FS2589-0042(23)02075-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EIScience%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20says%20that%20pigeons%20have%20advanced%20cognitive%20and%20attentional%20processes%20and%20can%20solve%20an%20%26quot%3Bexceptionally%20broad%26quot%3B%20range%20of%20categorization%20tasks%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETurner%20said%20the%20findings%20indicate%20that%20pigeons%20are%20natural%20%26quot%3Bincredibly%20efficient%26quot%3B%20learners%20who%20cannot%20generalize%20information%20the%20way%20humans%20can%2C%20according%20to%20the%20release.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20Turner%2C%20pigeons%20use%20associative%20learning%2C%20which%20connects%20two%20things%2C%20such%20as%20dogs%20understanding%20that%20they%20will%20receive%20a%20treat%20when%20they%20sit.%20Typically%2C%20associative%20learning%20is%20thought%20to%20be%20%26quot%3Btoo%20primitive%26quot%3B%20to%20do%20things%20like%20visual%20categorization%2C%20Turner%20said%20in%20the%20release%2C%20but%20apparently%20not%20for%20pigeons.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20researchers%20said%20humans%20tend%20to%20give%20up%20on%20tasks%20like%20those%20given%20to%20the%20pigeons%20when%20they%20can't%20come%20up%20with%20rules%20to%20make%20sense%20of%20the%20tasks.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%26quot%3BPigeons%20don't%20try%20to%20make%20rules.%20They%20just%20use%20this%20brute%20force%20way%20of%20trial%20and%20error%20and%20associative%20learning%20and%20in%20some%20specific%20types%20of%20tasks%20that%20helps%20them%20perform%20better%20than%20humans%2C%26quot%3B%20Turner%20said.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20noted%20that%20humans%20often%20%26quot%3Bcelebrate%20how%20smart%20we%20are%20that%20we%20designed%20artificial%20intelligence%3B%20at%20the%20same%20time%20we%20disparage%20pigeons%20as%20dim-witted%20animals.%26quot%3B%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBut%20the%20learning%20principles%20that%20guide%20the%20behaviors%20of%20these%20AI%20machines%20are%20pretty%20similar%20to%20what%20pigeons%20use%2C%26quot%3B%20Turner%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpigeons-mirror-ai-learning-patterns-researchers-say-2023-10%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1698513618000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F653d3600356802a56be6cbb9%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpigeons-mirror-ai-learning-patterns-researchers-say-2023-10%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Psychologists%20studying%20pigeons%20found%20that%20the%20birds%20problem%20solve%20in%20ways%20very%20similar%20to%20artificial%20intelligence.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22kniemeyer%40insider.com%20(Kenneth%20Niemeyer)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A266%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpigeons-mirror-ai-learning-patterns-researchers-say-2023-10%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Jacob%20Elordi%20Only%20Knew%20About%20Elvis%20Presley%20From%20%E2%80%98Lilo%20%26amp%3B%20Stitch%E2%80%99%20Before%20Starring%20in%20%E2%80%98Priscilla%E2%80%99%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1698512848000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fvariety.com%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2Felordi-stitch.jpg%3Fw%3D1000%26h%3D563%26crop%3D1%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fvariety.com%2F%3Fp%3D1235771719%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Before%20starring%20as%20Elvi